entries.title: South Korea Leader Dials Back Comments on Developing Nuclear Weapons
entries.description: Yoon Suk Yeol said in an interview at the World Economic Forum at Davos that his focus is on working with the U.S. on North Korea proliferation.

entries.title: European Support Grows for Sanctioning Iran's Revolutionary Guards
entries.description: The European Parliament urged member states to list Iran’s Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps as a terrorist organization, in a sign of growing support for new measures against Tehran.

entries.title: French Workers Strike in Protest of Macron's Plan to Raise Retirement Age
entries.description: Paris ground to a halt as thousands of people took to the streets in opposition of the French president’s pension-reform plans, in the start of what is expected to be a protracted showdown.

entries.title: Iraq Economy Reels as U.S. Moves Against Money Flows to Iran
entries.description: Iraqis are blaming a little-noticed policy change by the U.S. Treasury and the Federal Reserve Bank of New York for a weakening currency that has caused the price of food and imported goods to rise.

entries.title: For Ukraine, Dnipro Apartment Strike Becomes a Symbol of Russian Cruelty
entries.description: The deaths of civilians including children are drawing expressions of anger and resolve in Ukraine and the West as the war approaches the one-year mark.

entries.title: Philippine President Marcos Says He Is Seeking Ways to Defuse Tensions With China
entries.description: The country is increasing cooperation with the U.S. and developing stronger mechanisms to defuse disputes with China as it walks a fine line between the two superpowers, President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. said in an interview with The Wall Street Journal.

entries.title: Russia's Influence Wanes in Ex-Soviet States as It Pursues Ukraine War
entries.description: Tensions over a blockade of Nagorno-Karabakh show Moscow’s declining sway as it diverts resources to its invasion of Ukraine.

entries.title: Poland Suggests Sending German-Made Tanks to Ukraine Without Berlin's OK
entries.description: The statement is the latest sign of exasperation shared by the U.S. and its European allies that Germany’s hesitation over sending tanks will deprive Ukraine of critical resources in its war with Russia.

entries.title: New Zealand PM Jacinda Ardern to Step Down
entries.description: The prime minister said she will step down by Feb. 7 after 5½ years as leader.

entries.title: Mexico Bans California Startup's Experiments to Cool Atmosphere
entries.description: The solar-geoengineering project planned to inject sunlight-reflecting particles into the atmosphere with high-altitude balloons and intended to sell “cooling credits.”
